00:33:59,662 --> 00:34:02,046
[SPEAKER_07]: Daisy Cooper, respond to Stephen Flynn.

349
00:34:02,066 --> 00:34:03,047
[SPEAKER_07]: Do you talk to Stephen Flynn?

350
00:34:03,107 --> 00:34:06,152
[SPEAKER_03]: Well, on the question of tuition fees, we were punished for that.

351
00:34:06,352 --> 00:34:07,093
[SPEAKER_03]: That's democracy.

352
00:34:07,253 --> 00:34:07,674
[SPEAKER_03]: I get that.

353
00:34:07,774 --> 00:34:09,476
[SPEAKER_11]: Do you still believe in free tuition, though?

354
00:34:09,497 --> 00:34:12,381
[SPEAKER_03]: As I say, on the point of tuition fees, we were punished for that, right?

355
00:34:12,501 --> 00:34:13,382
[SPEAKER_03]: What's your position now?

356
00:34:13,402 --> 00:34:14,103
[SPEAKER_10]: What's your policy now?

357
00:34:14,324 --> 00:34:16,607
[SPEAKER_03]: In 2015, when we were out of coalition,

358
00:34:16,587 --> 00:34:25,459
[SPEAKER_03]: The thing that the Conservatives did on their own is they removed maintenance grants, the grants that were there for the poorest students to give them a shot at going to university.

359
00:34:25,799 --> 00:34:28,082
[SPEAKER_03]: And we have said that we would put those back in place.

360
00:34:28,102 --> 00:34:38,055
[SPEAKER_03]: But when it comes to education, we will not take lessons from the SNP, because under your watch, schools have fallen down the international rankings rapidly.

361
00:34:38,997 --> 00:34:43,367
